don't feel sad about themselves.

101
00:06:35,291 --> 00:06:37,375
Animals don't really
know what sorrow is,

102
00:06:37,458 --> 00:06:39,708
so then how can they feel sad?

103
00:06:39,791 --> 00:06:44,458
How come... humans are the
only ones to feel sadness?

104
00:06:44,541 --> 00:06:48,458
Yet they alone have the
potential to truly answer that.

105
00:06:48,541 --> 00:06:51,875
The answer to that.
What is it?

106
00:06:53,375 --> 00:06:55,041
So then the more
we pilot Fafner,

107
00:06:55,125 --> 00:06:57,125
the closer we come to dying?

108
00:06:57,208 --> 00:06:58,125
It's not death.

109
00:06:58,208 --> 00:06:59,791
Your body crystallizes
due to the

110
00:06:59,875 --> 00:07:01,500
chromosomal changes
it goes through.

111
00:07:01,583 --> 00:07:03,791
And how can you
call that being alive?

112
00:07:03,875 --> 00:07:06,333
You know what?
Maya's father was right!

113
00:07:06,416 --> 00:07:09,500
We're nothing but batteries
to mobilize the Fafners.

114
00:07:09,583 --> 00:07:13,541
And Sakura...
finally ran out of power...

115
00:07:13,625 --> 00:07:15,958
If Dr. Tohmi research
succeeds, we can prevent

116
00:07:16,041 --> 00:07:17,666
the assimilation from occurring.

117
00:07:17,750 --> 00:07:20,291
Too late...
Sakura's already...

118
00:07:24,291 --> 00:07:26,333
What are you doing?!

119
00:07:26,666 --> 00:07:29,000
I'm taking her home with me...

120
00:07:29,083 --> 00:07:30,250
Come on.

121
00:07:30,333 --> 00:07:31,791
Mother's going to take
you home now, Sakura.

122
00:07:31,875 --> 00:07:34,041
You can't!
She's not stable. If you--

123
00:07:34,125 --> 00:07:37,416
Don't you think Sakura's
fought enough already!

124
00:07:37,791 --> 00:07:38,958
Let her rest in peace.

125
00:07:39,041 --> 00:07:40,625
You're not helping her.

126
00:07:40,708 --> 00:07:41,666
Kiyomi!

127
00:07:41,750 --> 00:07:42,916
Kiyomi! Please!
Listen to me!

128
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:44,541
Let go!

129
00:07:44,625 --> 00:07:47,291
Kiyomi.
Kiyomi!

130
00:07:47,375 --> 00:07:48,625
Sakura...

131
00:07:49,750 --> 00:07:51,250
Kenji.

132
00:08:09,958 --> 00:08:11,916
Sakura...

133
00:08:20,166 --> 00:08:21,583
Kenji...

134
00:08:22,750 --> 00:08:26,083
You and I still have
a fight to settle, right?

135
00:08:29,250 --> 00:08:31,083
If a world where
there's constant

136
00:08:31,166 --> 00:08:33,666
fighting fills you
with sorrow then...

137
00:08:33,750 --> 00:08:35,250
What do you think
is the best way

138
00:08:35,333 --> 00:08:37,416
for you to erase this sorrow?

139
00:08:37,500 --> 00:08:38,833
To teach them.

140
00:08:38,916 --> 00:08:41,666
So that the Festum can
better understand our sorrow.

141
00:08:41,750 --> 00:08:43,083
Yes.

142
00:08:43,166 --> 00:08:45,541
Akane Makabe was the first
to come up with the idea.

143
00:08:45,625 --> 00:08:49,708
It's so simple a solution yet
very difficult at the same time.

144
00:08:49,791 --> 00:08:50,958
I don't believe it!

145
00:08:51,041 --> 00:08:52,708
Are you telling me that
that's what you've been

146
00:08:52,791 --> 00:08:54,791
trying to accomplish
during the battles?

147
00:08:54,875 --> 00:08:56,375
I'm afraid that,

148
00:08:56,458 --> 00:08:59,458
if I don't do this they'll end
up choosing the wrong feeling.

149
00:08:59,541 --> 00:09:01,375
A destructive emotion
that you can only

150
00:09:01,458 --> 00:09:03,583
feel if you are alive...

151
00:09:03,666 --> 00:09:05,666
That's hatred...

152
00:09:05,750 --> 00:09:07,250
If that's true,
the enemy already

153
00:09:07,333 --> 00:09:08,708
understands us fairly well?

154
00:09:08,791 --> 00:09:10,416
How am I supposed
to believe that?

155
00:09:10,500 --> 00:09:11,916
Because...

156
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:14,000
...I am the proof.

157
00:09:15,375 --> 00:09:17,375
Akane Makabe
showed the enemy life

158
00:09:17,458 --> 00:09:19,291
by treating them
like living things...

159
00:09:19,375 --> 00:09:21,083
It was the same thing with me.

160
00:09:21,166 --> 00:09:24,416
And that's how my mother
gave this island's MIR a life.

161
00:09:24,500 --> 00:09:27,541
I know you have your doubts.
But it's true.

162
00:09:27,625 --> 00:09:29,041
Because if this island's MIR

163
00:09:29,125 --> 00:09:31,291
wasn't able to
understand life...

164
00:09:31,375 --> 00:09:34,250
...there would've been no way
for me to have been born.

165
00:09:34,333 --> 00:09:35,541
Makes me wonder...

166
00:09:35,625 --> 00:09:38,000
Are we advancing
in the right direction.

167
00:09:38,083 --> 00:09:40,125
We made the island
for our posterity.

168
00:09:40,208 --> 00:09:41,791
And we used the enemy's power,

169
00:09:41,875 --> 00:09:43,416
and to ensure our
survival, we've been

170
00:09:43,500 --> 00:09:45,833
sacrificing our own children.

171
00:09:45,916 --> 00:09:48,500
We should be ashamed.

172
00:09:48,583 --> 00:09:50,166
The right power and path.

173
00:09:50,250 --> 00:09:52,750
You shall find it if
you search for it.

174
00:09:52,833 --> 00:09:55,250
And you're the kind of
person who can do that.

175
00:09:55,333 --> 00:09:58,708
The fact that you came here
to see me is proof of this.

176
00:09:58,791 --> 00:10:01,041
The path you
seek lies within you.

177
00:10:01,125 --> 00:10:04,458
Now you must find it.

178
00:10:06,416 --> 00:10:09,625
I see...
Poor Sakura...

179
00:10:10,291 --> 00:10:13,458
Um...
May I ask you something?

180
00:10:13,541 --> 00:10:15,333
Sure.
What is it?

181
00:10:15,416 --> 00:10:16,666
About Shoko...

182
00:10:16,750 --> 00:10:20,250
She wasn't your biological
daughter, am I right?

183
00:10:21,166 --> 00:10:22,708
No.

184
00:10:22,791 --> 00:10:24,875
They thought I had the
characteristics of someone

185
00:10:24,958 --> 00:10:26,333
who'd be good at
raising children.

186
00:10:26,416 --> 00:10:28,708
So the Albericht
Organization gave Shoko

187
00:10:28,791 --> 00:10:30,208
to me to raise as my own.

188
00:10:30,291 --> 00:10:32,541
And what about Kazuki and Maya?

189
00:10:32,625 --> 00:10:33,833
They're different.

190
00:10:33,916 --> 00:10:35,916
Shoko and Koyo
were the exceptions.

191
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:37,750
They were the only
children who weren't actually

192
00:10:37,833 --> 00:10:39,958
genetically related
to their parents.

193
00:10:40,041 --> 00:10:41,833
But they all have a
genetic component of the

194
00:10:41,916 --> 00:10:43,833
Festum in them, don't they?

195
00:10:43,916 --> 00:10:46,208
It was originally intended
to protect the genes

196
00:10:46,291 --> 00:10:47,958
from being polluted by MIR.

197
00:10:48,041 --> 00:10:49,458
If you don't
pilot a Fafner,

198
00:10:49,541 --> 00:10:52,083
then the MIR
factor isn't dangerous.

199
00:10:53,291 --> 00:10:56,958
I don't have it.
I'm missing the factor.

200
00:10:57,541 --> 00:10:59,958
That's why my integration
with the Siegfried System

201
00:11:00,041 --> 00:11:01,625
hasn't been completed yet...

202
00:11:01,708 --> 00:11:04,958
And why I still can't
pilot the Nothung Model.

203
00:11:05,666 --> 00:11:07,250
Canon.

204
00:11:07,333 --> 00:11:11,791
I just want to...
be like everyone else...

205
00:11:14,333 --> 00:11:15,625
There...

206
00:11:16,500 --> 00:11:18,416
That's all of it.

207
00:11:21,541 --> 00:11:25,125
I wonder what happens
at the end of this story.

208
00:11:28,708 --> 00:11:29,750
You know what?

209
00:11:29,833 --> 00:11:32,375
I'm positive it'll
have a happy ending.

210
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:36,375
After all, that's
what I'm fighting for.

211
00:11:47,958 --> 00:11:50,791
The Mark Sein is able to
connect the best with the core.

212
00:11:50,875 --> 00:11:52,458
But it's not because
it's more like the

213
00:11:52,541 --> 00:11:54,875
Festums than other Fafners.

214
00:11:54,958 --> 00:11:57,083
Then is it possible to
apply the power-gain

215
00:11:57,166 --> 00:11:59,375
release
to other machines?

216
